parts:
{
  "prompt": "A scientific illustration showing the concept of trisomy 21 (Down syndrome) and its correction using allele-specific CRISPR-Cas9. The image is divided in two parts. On the left, show a cell with three copies of chromosome 21 (labeled P, M1, and M2), representing trisomy. Highlight the extra chromosome in red to show it's the target. On the right, show the same cell after allele-specific CRISPR-Cas9 treatment, now with only two chromosomes (P and M1), indicating that the extra M2 allele has been removed. Include simple labels and a DNA scissor icon representing the CRISPR-Cas9 system. The style is clean, educational, and suitable for a research presentation.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "2D digital scientific illustration showing human chromosome 21 disomy after successful CRISPR-Cas9 correction. The image displays two X-shaped structures, both in light blue, representing the normal pair of chromosome 21, with the absence of a third (extra) chromosome. The background is clean and white, and a label reads 'Corrected disomy - 2 copies of chromosome 21'.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "An infographic in a clean scientific style, white background, displaying two panels side-by-side. On the left panel, show three chromosome 21s (two blue, one red labeled 'Extra copy') with the title 'Before CRISPR-Cas9 (47,XY,+21)'. On the right panel, show only two blue chromosome 21s with the title 'After CRISPR-Cas9 (46,XY)'. Add a subtle arrow between the panels indicating transition. Minimal, high-contrast design suitable for academic presentation.",
  "size": "1024x768"
}
